</style>

<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Colgate-Palmolive (CL)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Colgate-Palmolive — using actual financials, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {meta.published} · Data: Latest Financials</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV !== null ? roundedIV.toFixed(2) : "N/A"}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : "N/A"} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${revenueHistory[4] !== null ? (revenueHistory[4] / 1000).toFixed(1) : "N/A"}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${fcfHistory[4] !== null ? (fcfHistory[4] / 1000).toFixed(1) : "N/A"}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsHistory[4] !== null ? epsHistory[4].toFixed(2) : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{marginHistory[4] !== null ? marginHistory[4].operating : "N/A"}%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) : "N/A"}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Colgate-Palmolive generated <strong>${baseFCF !== null ? (baseFCF / 1000).toFixed(2) : "N/A"} billion</strong> in free cash flow in the most recent period. This is real cash the business produces after paying for operations and capital expenditures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This assumes a moderate, stable growth path consistent with a mature fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) company benefiting from pricing power and emerging market expansion.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> — roughly matching long-term inflation. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong> to capture all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This aligns with Colgate's historically low beta (low volatility) compared to the 10Y Treasury (4.18%) plus a conservative equity risk premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(2) : "N/A"}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding : "N/A"}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Colgate operates in highly mature markets but enjoys immense brand loyalty and pricing power. High single-digit growth is unrealistic without major acquisitions, but 5% is an achievable mix of modest volume growth, price increases, and margin optimization.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. With a very low beta (typically around 0.4-0.5), Colgate's cost of equity is exceptionally low. A 7% discount rate reflects its status as a defensive, recession-resistant dividend aristocrat.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth and inflation hover around 2-3%. Assuming a consumer staples giant grows at 2% in perpetuity is a very safe assumption, meaning it simply maintains its purchasing power relative to global inflation over the decades.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
